        <section class="question-long-text" data-uuid="549858c7d8b049f399ad5a8462f12530">
            <object type="text/html" data="../../assets/widgets/long_text_question/index.html" class="widget" data-uuid="e801fedbf8c24481b1400a377ff7c238">
                <param name="configFile" value="../../widget_data/config/e801fedbf8c24481b1400a377ff7c238.json" />
            </object>
        </section>
        <p data-uuid="72e8df6f542e4f9982aef0ca242085eb">The government responded to these concerns with new laws. Immigration legislation, such as the Emergency Quota Act of 1921, limited the total number of immigrants allowed into the country. It also favored immigrants from western Europe. The National Origins Act of 1924 banned immigration from East Asia entirely. It also further reduced the number of immigrants allowed to enter the country. These laws caused a dramatic drop in immigration to the United States.<br />
        </p>
